title: Opinion
content:
Typical Question Words


  • What is your opinion?
  • To what extent do you agree or disagree?
  • Do you agree or disagree?
  • Do the advantages outweigh disadvantages?
  • Positive or negative development


Example Question

Nowadays, more people are choosing to socialise online rather than face to face.


Is

this a positive or negative development?



Essay Structure

Opinion Essay

There can be four opinions to this type of essay.

1. Yes (Clear Opinion)
2. No (Clear Opinion)
3. Large extent Yes (80% - 20% Mixed Opinion)
4. Large extent No (80% - 20% Mixed Opinion)


To what extent do you agree or disagree


Do you agree or disagree?


Do the advantages outweigh disadvantages?

There can be four reaction to this type of essay.

1. Advantages outweigh disadvantages (Only Advantages)
2. Disadvantages outweigh advantages (Only disadvantages)
3. To large extent advantages outweigh (80% - 20%)
4. To large extent disadvantages outweigh (80% - 20%)


Positive or negative development

title: Advantage and Disadvantages
content:
Typical Question Words

  • Discuss the advantages and disadvantages and give your own opinion.
  • Discuss the advantages and disadvantages.


Example Question

A lot of places in the world rely on tourism as a main source of income. Unfortunately, tourism can also be a source of problems if it is not managed correctly.


Describe the advantages and disadvantages of tourism in the modern world.



Essay Structure

title: Cause and Effect or Solution
content:
Typical Question Words

  • Cause and solution.
  • Cause and effect.


Example Question

The percentage of overweight children in western society has increased by almost 20% in the last ten years.


Discuss the causes and effects of this disturbing trend.



Essay Structure

title: Discussion
content:
Typical Question Words

  • Discuss both points of view and give your opinion.


Example Question

A growing number of people feel that animals should not be exploited by people and that they should have the same rights as humans, while others argue that humans must employ animals to satisfy their various needs, including uses for food and research.


Discuss both views and give your opinion.



Essay Structure

title: Two-Part Question
content:
Typical Question Words

  • There will be a one statement and different sorts of questions you may be asked.


Example Question

In education and employment, some people work harder than others.


Why do some people work harder?

Is it always a good thing to work hard? Discuss both views and give your opinion.



Essay Structure
